WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.011 --> 00:00:13.888
<i>There are many important birthdays</i>
<i>during one's life.</i>

2
00:00:13.972 --> 00:00:16.725
<i>Your first. then ten. double digits.</i>

3
00:00:16.808 --> 00:00:18.393
<i>Thirteen. obviously.</i>

4
00:00:18.476 --> 00:00:20.854
<i>Fifteen or sixteen.</i>
<i>depending on your heritage.</i>

5
00:00:20.937 --> 00:00:23.398
<i>and then the big one-eight.</i>

6
00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:31.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

7
00:00:37.120 --> 00:00:39.998
How was your body scrub?

8
00:00:40.081 --> 00:00:44.127
My almost-adult skin is feeling
as soft as a newborn baby.

9
00:00:44.753 --> 00:00:49.841
Now. is your glow from your facial
or because things between you and Juliana

10
00:00:49.924 --> 00:00:52.010
are heating back up
after the fashion show?

11
00:00:52.093 --> 00:00:54.304
The facial.

12
00:00:54.387 --> 00:00:58.224
Honestly. I would die of happiness
if we could be more than friends.

13
00:00:58.308 --> 00:01:02.729
But after the way I hurt her last year.
she would have to make the first move.

14
00:01:02.812 --> 00:01:04.522
What about you and Min Ho?

15
00:01:04.606 --> 00:01:05.482
I don't know.

16
00:01:05.565 --> 00:01:09.569
Even if he wanted to make it work.
how could it if I'm going to NYU?

17
00:01:09.652 --> 00:01:13.615
Anyway. you still haven't RSVP'd
to my birthday party invite.

18
00:01:13.698 --> 00:01:15.700
Yeah. about that…

19
00:01:17.202 --> 00:01:19.537
There's no way you're not coming
to my 18th birthday party.

20
00:01:19.621 --> 00:01:20.789
I know. I'm sorry.

21
00:01:20.872 --> 00:01:23.333
I already promised Yisoo
I would house-sit on Saturday.

22
00:01:23.416 --> 00:01:25.877
But I have an entire itinerary
laid out in my journal.

23
00:01:25.960 --> 00:01:28.838
I even found
the perfect party dress. Look.

24
00:01:29.881 --> 00:01:31.925
- Camellia pink.
- Mm.

25
00:01:32.008 --> 00:01:33.343
Why camellia?

26
00:01:33.426 --> 00:01:35.303
It was my mom's favorite flower.

27
00:01:35.386 --> 00:01:37.263
Birthdays always make me think of her.

28
00:01:37.347 --> 00:01:39.724
I think she'd like that
I'm celebrating with the friends

29
00:01:39.808 --> 00:01:41.643
who helped me become the person I am.

30
00:01:42.352 --> 00:01:44.145
You are definitely one of those friends.

31
00:01:44.229 --> 00:01:46.064
Oh. Kitty.

32
00:01:46.689 --> 00:01:47.607
I still can't go.

33
00:01:47.690 --> 00:01:49.400
- Yuri!
- Shh!

34
00:01:49.484 --> 00:01:51.027
I'm sorry.

35
00:01:52.529 --> 00:01:54.447
<i>Okay. well. Yuri's dead to me.</i>

36
00:01:54.531 --> 00:01:57.826
<i>Kidding. But come on. it's my birthday.</i>

37
00:02:01.079 --> 00:02:02.497
Oh. Dae. I'm so glad you're here.

38
00:02:02.580 --> 00:02:05.917
I think that my birthday invite
got lost in your spam folder.

39
00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:07.252
You'll be there. right?

40
00:02:07.335 --> 00:02:12.132
I wish I could.
but I have a thing at my dad's restaurant.

41
00:02:12.215 --> 00:02:13.925
- Yep.
- Oh.

42
00:02:14.008 --> 00:02:17.137
- But I only turn 18 once.
- Sorry.

43
00:02:19.264 --> 00:02:22.851
Should I have sent out
save the dates? Ooh!

44
00:02:22.934 --> 00:02:25.145
Ah. ah. ah! Those are for Jin.

45
00:02:25.228 --> 00:02:27.397
Mm. You're trying to <i>butter </i>him up.

46
00:02:27.480 --> 00:02:30.650
Make him feel <i>batter</i>
by showing how much you <i>knead </i>him.

47
00:02:30.733 --> 00:02:32.527
- That was cute. I like that.
- Thank you.

48
00:02:32.610 --> 00:02:35.446
I've been leaving him treats and gifts
to show him I care.

49
00:02:35.530 --> 00:02:39.325
Hm. Well. I think a demonstration of love
beats a declaration of love any day.

50
00:02:39.409 --> 00:02:41.911
Look at you
with your soon-to-be-adult wisdom.

51
00:02:41.995 --> 00:02:43.121
- Speaking of…
- So. Kitty…

52
00:02:43.204 --> 00:02:44.622
- I have some bad news.
- No.

53
00:02:44.706 --> 00:02:46.332
- I don't think I'm gonna be able to…
- No.

54
00:02:46.416 --> 00:02:47.458
- …make it to your--
- No!

55
00:02:47.542 --> 00:02:49.419
You are coming to my birthday party.

56
00:02:49.502 --> 00:02:50.920
I can't.

57
00:02:51.004 --> 00:02:53.381
I… I have a thing for track.

58
00:02:53.464 --> 00:02:55.466
It's a… It's a track thing. So…

59
00:02:56.050 --> 00:02:59.429
- Hm.
- Please stop looking at me like that.

60
00:02:59.512 --> 00:03:04.058
First Yuri blows off my party.
and then Dae. and now you?

61
00:03:05.643 --> 00:03:07.395
Oh my God.

62
00:03:07.478 --> 00:03:09.647
Are you throwing me a surprise party?

63
00:03:09.731 --> 00:03:11.399
No one's ever thrown me one before!

64
00:03:11.482 --> 00:03:14.152
Maybe that's because you're
always in everyone's business. Kitty.

65
00:03:14.235 --> 00:03:16.112
What's the ruse?
Where? What should I wear?

66
00:03:16.196 --> 00:03:18.448
- There's this dress that--
- I've said too much.

67
00:03:18.531 --> 00:03:20.617
And don't go digging
for information. okay?

68
00:03:20.700 --> 00:03:22.869
You're gonna have to wait
and see what we have planned.

69
00:03:24.495 --> 00:03:25.914
<i>Me. wait and see?</i>

70
00:03:25.997 --> 00:03:29.375
<i>Yeah. tall order.</i>
<i>But fine. I'll play along.</i>

71
00:03:39.260 --> 00:03:42.055
NYU. here I come!

72
00:03:42.138 --> 00:03:46.184
Kitty. you have so much to celebrate.
NYU. your 18th birthday.

73
00:03:46.267 --> 00:03:47.936
Sorry to miss your party.

74
00:03:48.019 --> 00:03:51.773
Yeah. we have a thing
across town on Saturday. so…

75
00:03:51.856 --> 00:03:53.483
<i>Where </i>across town?

76
00:03:54.150 --> 00:03:55.944
Hongdae? Jamsil?

77
00:03:57.153 --> 00:03:58.529
Oh God. look at the time.

78
00:04:00.823 --> 00:04:02.909
- Is this a dressy thing you're going to?
- Help.

79
00:04:02.992 --> 00:04:03.826
Or is it more--

80
00:04:15.797 --> 00:04:16.631
- Hey.
- Hi.

81
00:04:17.966 --> 00:04:19.968
I hope you got my birthday invite.

82
00:04:20.760 --> 00:04:23.763
And I hope it wasn't weird
that I sent it to you.

83
00:04:23.846 --> 00:04:27.308
No. I… I'm glad you did.

84
00:04:27.392 --> 00:04:30.395
But I can't make it.

85
00:04:31.104 --> 00:04:33.940
Oh. I get it. I mean. everyone's busy.

86
00:04:34.023 --> 00:04:38.653
Yes. I actually decided to go visit
my mom in LA for winter break.

87
00:04:38.736 --> 00:04:40.571
And meet up with a few music contacts.

88
00:04:41.781 --> 00:04:43.157
That's great.

89
00:04:43.658 --> 00:04:46.244
I'm… really excited for you.

90
00:04:47.745 --> 00:04:49.038
See you later.

91
00:04:55.044 --> 00:04:55.962
All right. mate.

92
00:04:56.045 --> 00:04:58.840
When are you gonna fess up
and tell her you want her back?

93
00:04:59.465 --> 00:05:02.468
I was going to. all right?
At the fashion show.

94
00:05:03.469 --> 00:05:05.972
But then she got the email from NYU.

95
00:05:07.098 --> 00:05:08.308
So?

96
00:05:08.391 --> 00:05:10.226
So now it doesn't matter.

97
00:05:10.310 --> 00:05:12.395
Her future is mapped out. literally.

98
00:05:13.062 --> 00:05:14.063
She's happy.

99
00:05:15.940 --> 00:05:17.525
And I'm not about to ruin that.

100
00:05:27.368 --> 00:05:30.538
I think a "congratulations" are in order.
don't you?

101
00:05:30.621 --> 00:05:33.124
Honestly. I didn't see this coming.

102
00:05:33.207 --> 00:05:35.168
Jiwon literally cried when she found out.

103
00:05:35.251 --> 00:05:36.878
Kitty. you told him?

104
00:05:37.420 --> 00:05:41.090
- Well. I suppose you're disappointed.
- Why would I be?

105
00:05:41.174 --> 00:05:42.383
Alex. no. this is not--

106
00:05:42.467 --> 00:05:45.094
- NYU is perfectly respectable.
- I'm happy Jiwon's pregnant.

107
00:05:45.178 --> 00:05:46.387
Wait.

108
00:05:46.471 --> 00:05:47.472
What?

109
00:05:49.515 --> 00:05:53.394
Okay. I've been seeing Miss Ahn
since the summer.

110
00:05:54.437 --> 00:05:55.772
We're in love.

111
00:05:56.814 --> 00:05:58.441
And I'm gonna be a dad.

112
00:06:00.318 --> 00:06:03.738
- You two are practically kids yourselves.
- We're older than you were.

113
00:06:05.198 --> 00:06:07.158
I'm sorry. I… I didn't mean that.

114
00:06:07.241 --> 00:06:09.410
I'm gonna let you two talk.

115
00:06:12.789 --> 00:06:13.956
Look.

116
00:06:14.040 --> 00:06:16.292
I don't know if I'm ready.

117
00:06:16.376 --> 00:06:20.046
But what I do know
is that I'm gonna be there.

118
00:06:24.425 --> 00:06:29.222
I hope you know…
if I'd had any idea about you.

119
00:06:29.305 --> 00:06:32.100
I would have dropped everything
to be in your life.

120
00:06:32.183 --> 00:06:33.393
Everything.

121
00:06:36.437 --> 00:06:38.022
I'm glad you get this chance

122
00:06:39.482 --> 00:06:41.067
to be the father I wasn't.

123
00:06:43.611 --> 00:06:45.947
Be there for all the important firsts.

124
00:06:46.906 --> 00:06:48.408
Well. I was hoping that

125
00:06:49.659 --> 00:06:52.328
maybe we could
share those firsts together.

126
00:06:52.829 --> 00:06:54.288
Grandfather.

127
00:07:07.135 --> 00:07:10.388
- It's Bora.
- What. what? What?

128
00:07:11.139 --> 00:07:15.017
She said Kitty called our restaurant
and used a fake voice

129
00:07:15.101 --> 00:07:18.396
to ask if we had a birthday party
booked on Saturday night.

130
00:07:18.479 --> 00:07:23.359
This morning I "accidentally" left

131
00:07:23.443 --> 00:07:27.113
a sky-diving brochure
in the girls' common room.

132
00:07:27.196 --> 00:07:28.448
Ah.

133
00:07:28.531 --> 00:07:32.910
Dae. thank you for helping me
catch up on my studies.

134
00:07:32.994 --> 00:07:35.580
I might actually get into uni.

135
00:07:37.874 --> 00:07:40.001
I'd do anything for you. Eunice.

136
00:07:41.669 --> 00:07:45.882
Like be my date
for Kitty's surprise party?

137
00:07:48.634 --> 00:07:50.344
I thought you'd never ask.

138
00:07:53.389 --> 00:07:55.933
Hey. are you okay? Is something wrong?

139
00:07:56.434 --> 00:07:58.728
You texted 911!

140
00:07:59.937 --> 00:08:04.525
I meant SOS911. the girl group.

141
00:08:05.067 --> 00:08:08.613
Soo-jin called me.
They got into a huge fight with your dad.

142
00:08:08.696 --> 00:08:11.616
Sounds like him. but…

143
00:08:11.699 --> 00:08:16.204
I told the girls
everything you did for me.

144
00:08:16.287 --> 00:08:19.665
Now they want you to be their new manager.

145
00:08:20.374 --> 00:08:24.837
You do this. your dad's gonna have
to hold himself from fainting.

146
00:08:26.422 --> 00:08:29.258
It would be fun to mess with his head.

147
00:08:30.092 --> 00:08:33.262
but you and I are just getting started
with our music stuff.

148
00:08:33.346 --> 00:08:36.557
I still haven't told my dad
I'm not pursuing engineering.

149
00:08:36.641 --> 00:08:40.686
Just because my career is over
doesn't mean yours should be too.

150
00:08:44.857 --> 00:08:48.486
<i>Happy birthday. dear Kitty </i>

151
00:08:48.569 --> 00:08:49.695
<i>Happy birthday to you </i>

152
00:08:49.779 --> 00:08:51.572
<i>Anyone figured out</i>
<i>what you're supposed to do</i>

153
00:08:51.656 --> 00:08:53.157
<i>when people sing "Happy Birthday"?</i>

154
00:08:53.241 --> 00:08:56.452
If you wish away my heartburn.
I'll name our baby after you.

155
00:08:59.080 --> 00:09:02.667
I'm so glad we got the chance
to celebrate before your big day.

156
00:09:02.750 --> 00:09:06.462
And I'm so glad that Professor Lee
took the news about the baby well.

157
00:09:06.546 --> 00:09:08.130
He's super happy for us.

158
00:09:08.839 --> 00:09:13.344
but teachers aren't allowed to date.
so one of us might need to leave KISS.

159
00:09:14.178 --> 00:09:18.099
- Actually?
- If it comes to it… I'll quit.

160
00:09:22.353 --> 00:09:25.189
Right now. Jiwon and I
are just focusing on what's important.

161
00:09:26.107 --> 00:09:27.191
The baby.

162
00:09:28.609 --> 00:09:31.153
Look at that poor woman over there.

163
00:09:31.237 --> 00:09:33.364
She's been rocking her baby
this entire time

164
00:09:33.447 --> 00:09:35.241
and she hasn't had one bite of food.

165
00:09:35.324 --> 00:09:37.368
How am I supposed to do this?

166
00:09:37.451 --> 00:09:39.537
I don't know anything
about being a mother.

167
00:09:39.620 --> 00:09:41.247
No. you're going to be great.

168
00:09:42.373 --> 00:09:46.294
You know you could talk to somebody
who does know about being a mother.

169
00:09:46.377 --> 00:09:49.046
My <i>halmoni </i>would disown me if she knew.

170
00:09:49.130 --> 00:09:52.300
Professor Lee is a tough cookie.
and he came around.

171
00:09:52.383 --> 00:09:54.093
Maybe Imo-Halmoni will too.

172
00:09:54.176 --> 00:09:56.470
Please. Jiwon. can I call her?

173
00:10:00.349 --> 00:10:02.852
If you like my peanut butter cookies.
you'll love these.

174
00:10:02.935 --> 00:10:06.689
You don't have to keep bringing me treats.
But thanks.

175
00:10:07.356 --> 00:10:09.650
Sorry. I have a lot going on right now.

176
00:10:11.360 --> 00:10:13.237
Are you working on your uni apps?

177
00:10:13.321 --> 00:10:14.864
Lee told me my chances aren't great

178
00:10:14.947 --> 00:10:17.617
now that I'm not a track star
and my résumé's basically blank.

179
00:10:18.284 --> 00:10:20.328
I wish there was something I could do.

180
00:10:21.871 --> 00:10:24.665
Well. maybe Kitty's party
will be a good distraction?

181
00:10:24.749 --> 00:10:25.833
You're still coming. right?

182
00:10:25.916 --> 00:10:29.545
Yeah. I can't wait to see
the look on her face.

183
00:10:40.556 --> 00:10:43.643
Who's this?

184
00:10:43.726 --> 00:10:47.229
This is Alex. we work together.

185
00:10:47.897 --> 00:10:49.023
You've got this.

186
00:10:51.734 --> 00:10:54.320
He's going to be my baby's father.

187
00:10:55.571 --> 00:10:56.781
Grandma…

188
00:10:58.741 --> 00:11:00.326
I'm pregnant.

189
00:11:01.744 --> 00:11:02.745
What?

190
00:11:13.381 --> 00:11:15.049
Oh my God!

191
00:11:15.675 --> 00:11:18.844
Are you trying
to send me out of this world?

192
00:11:18.928 --> 00:11:22.556
You're just determined. aren't you?
Just determined.

193
00:11:24.934 --> 00:11:30.064
I thought you wanted
to go to Seoul for work.

194
00:11:31.232 --> 00:11:34.402
If you were just going
to meet a man and start a family.

195
00:11:34.485 --> 00:11:36.237
you could have stayed in Bukjeon!

196
00:11:36.320 --> 00:11:39.949
I just wanted
to find someone I loved on my own.

197
00:11:40.032 --> 00:11:41.992
Is that so wrong?

198
00:11:42.076 --> 00:11:44.745
Oh. I see.

199
00:11:44.829 --> 00:11:47.873
You don't need me anymore!

200
00:11:49.959 --> 00:11:50.960
Grandma…

201
00:11:56.048 --> 00:11:59.051
I need you more than ever now.

202
00:12:02.096 --> 00:12:05.141
We're both matchmakers.

203
00:12:06.183 --> 00:12:08.936
They're a perfect couple!

204
00:12:09.645 --> 00:12:15.234
Alex will take care of Jiwon.
just like you always have.

205
00:12:21.031 --> 00:12:23.367
Ah. Oh.

206
00:12:23.451 --> 00:12:25.202
Oh my. you speak so well.

207
00:12:25.828 --> 00:12:27.663
You're all grown up.

208
00:12:31.417 --> 00:12:33.169
I really

209
00:12:34.754 --> 00:12:36.130
love Jiwon.

210
00:12:38.758 --> 00:12:41.761
And I would really love for us all

211
00:12:42.428 --> 00:12:44.180
to become a family.

212
00:12:52.855 --> 00:12:55.775
What a handsome chin.

213
00:12:56.734 --> 00:12:57.651
Okay.

214
00:12:57.735 --> 00:12:58.694
Okay.

215
00:13:11.499 --> 00:13:13.876
<i>Ugh. I hate being in the dark.</i>

216
00:13:13.959 --> 00:13:15.419
<i>But I guess I'm pretty flattered</i>

217
00:13:15.503 --> 00:13:18.297
<i>that my friends are trying so hard</i>
<i>to throw me off the scent.</i>

218
00:13:18.380 --> 00:13:20.257
<i>And it's actually working.</i>

219
00:13:20.341 --> 00:13:22.802
<i>Just hang in there a little longer. Kitty.</i>

220
00:13:27.807 --> 00:13:28.808
Hello.

221
00:13:28.891 --> 00:13:30.810
Happy birthday. Kitty.

222
00:13:30.893 --> 00:13:33.270
Thank you. You're up early.

223
00:13:33.354 --> 00:13:36.148
My boss just emailed.
and she loves the book.

224
00:13:36.232 --> 00:13:39.568
Of course she does. Wait. that's amazing.

225
00:13:39.652 --> 00:13:43.113
So I have that dedication page.
like. on lock. right?

226
00:13:43.197 --> 00:13:45.658
'Cause that would be
a pretty sick birthday present.

227
00:13:45.741 --> 00:13:47.993
If I ever get published.

228
00:13:48.077 --> 00:13:50.204
I'm gonna dedicate the first book to Mom.

229
00:13:50.287 --> 00:13:51.664
<i>But you get the sequel.</i>

230
00:13:51.747 --> 00:13:55.751
Yes. I've edged out Margot.
I'm so proud of you. sister.

231
00:13:55.835 --> 00:13:57.253
Thank you.

232
00:13:57.336 --> 00:14:00.339
Oh. um. that reminds me.
Uh. Peter says hi.

233
00:14:01.382 --> 00:14:02.258
Wait. what?

234
00:14:02.842 --> 00:14:04.844
- Peter and I have some news.
- What is it?

235
00:14:04.927 --> 00:14:06.887
Obviously there's things we have
to figure out.

236
00:14:06.971 --> 00:14:08.556
but we are gonna make it work.

237
00:14:08.639 --> 00:14:11.183
Love is worth the risk. right?

238
00:14:11.267 --> 00:14:13.936
This is the best news ever.

239
00:14:14.019 --> 00:14:15.062
<i>I love you so much.</i>

240
00:14:15.145 --> 00:14:18.440
I hope you have an amazing birthday.
And I'll talk to you soon.

241
00:14:18.524 --> 00:14:20.568
Love you too. Bye.

242
00:14:20.651 --> 00:14:22.444
<i>Call it a matchmaker's intuition.</i>

243
00:14:22.528 --> 00:14:25.781
<i>but I knew Peter and Lara Jean</i>
<i>would find their way back to each other.</i>

244
00:14:25.865 --> 00:14:27.658
<i>even if they had to go the long way.</i>

245
00:14:27.741 --> 00:14:29.410
<i>Best gift ever.</i>

246
00:14:31.036 --> 00:14:32.246
Okay. how about…

247
00:14:33.581 --> 00:14:37.167
Okay. pretty good. I think we could sell
it a bit more if we added some shock.

248
00:14:37.251 --> 00:14:39.253
Like. almost dead.

249
00:14:43.257 --> 00:14:46.510
I'm sorry that I couldn't be more chill
about my surprise party.

250
00:14:46.594 --> 00:14:49.138
I just thought that
if I knew what I was going into.

251
00:14:49.221 --> 00:14:52.516
I could let go of the one
that I wrote in my Sunset List.

252
00:14:53.058 --> 00:14:56.520
It's not like you haven't crossed off
a bunch of other things. right?

253
00:14:56.604 --> 00:15:00.232
Yeah. but none of them
really went the way I imagined.

254
00:15:00.316 --> 00:15:03.235
Like. when I pictured talking
to Imo-Halmoni in Korean.

255
00:15:03.319 --> 00:15:06.572
I never thought I'd be hard-selling Alex
as Jiwon's baby daddy.

256
00:15:07.698 --> 00:15:10.951
Or when I defined
my relationship with Min Ho.

257
00:15:11.035 --> 00:15:14.288
I never thought
we would do that just to break up.

258
00:15:18.834 --> 00:15:22.630
I know you're bummed.
but tonight's not about him.

259
00:15:23.130 --> 00:15:24.340
It's about <i>you</i>.

260
00:15:25.341 --> 00:15:26.508
You're right.

261
00:15:27.551 --> 00:15:31.847
And thank you for whatever
diabolical plan you have in store for me.

262
00:15:43.484 --> 00:15:46.570
<i>Sleeping on my own. what a crime</i>

263
00:15:47.571 --> 00:15:50.199
<i>Losin' self-control every time…</i>

264
00:15:51.867 --> 00:15:53.869
Happy birthday!

265
00:15:57.331 --> 00:15:58.958
This is incredible!

266
00:15:59.833 --> 00:16:03.212
Wait. so all of the clues. they were lies?

267
00:16:03.295 --> 00:16:05.839
More like misdirections.

268
00:16:05.923 --> 00:16:08.884
Well… you gave us no choice.

269
00:16:10.302 --> 00:16:11.345
You came.

270
00:16:11.428 --> 00:16:15.265
We all decided
the only way to surprise you is

271
00:16:15.349 --> 00:16:16.475
to keep you guessing.

272
00:16:19.770 --> 00:16:20.896
It's called a Kittytini!

273
00:16:20.980 --> 00:16:24.483
- My very own mocktail! Thank you.
- Uh-huh.

274
00:16:28.028 --> 00:16:30.030
Are these camellias?

275
00:16:30.114 --> 00:16:31.490
Min Ho brought them in.

276
00:16:37.579 --> 00:16:38.789
Now go change.

277
00:16:39.415 --> 00:16:41.458
- My dress?
- Mm-hmm.

278
00:16:41.542 --> 00:16:42.793
Thank you!

279
00:16:43.335 --> 00:16:44.837
Thank you. everybody.

280
00:16:44.920 --> 00:16:46.922
This is amazing.

281
00:16:50.634 --> 00:16:51.802
Yo.

282
00:16:52.803 --> 00:16:54.680
Good job keeping Kitty in the dark.

283
00:16:54.763 --> 00:16:57.558
Right? That girl's like
a human lie detector.

284
00:16:58.809 --> 00:17:02.980
Hey. so. are you still planning on
interning for your dad next semester?

285
00:17:03.063 --> 00:17:03.897
No.

286
00:17:03.981 --> 00:17:07.067
I mean. don't get me wrong.
I would look delectable in pinstripes.

287
00:17:07.151 --> 00:17:10.863
but I'd much rather just enjoy
my last semester of high school.

288
00:17:10.946 --> 00:17:11.947
Why?

289
00:17:12.823 --> 00:17:14.450
I might need a favor.

290
00:17:14.533 --> 00:17:17.745
<i>Wanna take me for a ride</i>

291
00:17:17.828 --> 00:17:21.123
<i>Do you got more than meets the eye?</i>

292
00:17:21.832 --> 00:17:23.584
<i>But. baby. come and take a seat</i>

293
00:17:23.667 --> 00:17:25.544
<i>Need you to inspire me</i>

294
00:17:25.627 --> 00:17:29.423
<i>I'm only giving you one try</i>

295
00:17:29.506 --> 00:17:30.966
<i>Ready. set. go</i>

296
00:17:31.050 --> 00:17:32.801
<i>So hot. like summertime</i>

297
00:17:32.885 --> 00:17:34.595
<i>I can make you melt</i>

298
00:17:34.678 --> 00:17:36.430
<i>One look. you're hypnotized</i>

299
00:17:36.513 --> 00:17:38.098
<i>Baby. I can tell</i>

300
00:17:38.182 --> 00:17:39.850
<i>I'm running through your mind</i>

301
00:17:39.933 --> 00:17:41.894
<i>So catch me if you can</i>

302
00:17:45.939 --> 00:17:48.442
<i>Text me. though they miss me</i>
<i>They can't kiss me</i>

303
00:17:51.612 --> 00:17:53.614
<i>XO. XO. XO. XO</i>

304
00:17:54.239 --> 00:17:56.533
- Okay. time for gifts!
- Yay!

305
00:17:56.617 --> 00:17:58.786
- Happy birthday. Kitty.
- Thank you.

306
00:17:59.703 --> 00:18:00.704
A lock?

307
00:18:00.788 --> 00:18:06.043
Because we first met at Namsan Tower.
and I hope our friendship lasts forever.

308
00:18:06.126 --> 00:18:08.253
Aww.

309
00:18:08.337 --> 00:18:10.214
- I love it.
- Okay. mine.

310
00:18:13.509 --> 00:18:17.221
So I'm launching my new line with
the dress you wore at the fashion show.

311
00:18:17.304 --> 00:18:19.264
and this label's gonna be on it.

312
00:18:19.348 --> 00:18:20.599
Yuri!

313
00:18:21.266 --> 00:18:22.476
Mm.

314
00:18:26.814 --> 00:18:28.607
Aww. cupcakes!

315
00:18:28.690 --> 00:18:30.776
It's to remember the first night we met.

316
00:18:30.859 --> 00:18:34.363
when you absolutely demolished
that cupcake tower.

317
00:18:34.446 --> 00:18:37.741
And because you're the sweetest
and messiest person I know.

318
00:18:38.700 --> 00:18:41.495
Was the point of these gifts
to make me cry?

319
00:18:41.578 --> 00:18:45.249
Well. we each wanted to get you something
to show how much you mean to us.

320
00:18:45.332 --> 00:18:46.750
Yeah. it was Min Ho's idea.

321
00:18:48.001 --> 00:18:49.294
That's so thoughtful.

322
00:18:50.170 --> 00:18:52.339
Thank you. guys.

323
00:18:52.422 --> 00:18:54.925
<i>When people keep repeating</i>

324
00:18:55.008 --> 00:18:57.761
<i>That you'll never fall in love</i>

325
00:18:57.845 --> 00:19:00.222
<i>When everybody keeps retreating</i>

326
00:19:00.305 --> 00:19:02.975
<i>But you can't seem to get enough</i>

327
00:19:03.684 --> 00:19:05.853
<i>Let my love open the door</i>

328
00:19:06.353 --> 00:19:07.479
<i>To your heart</i>

329
00:19:14.403 --> 00:19:15.320
Damn.

330
00:19:15.946 --> 00:19:18.323
Future CEO Jin really works.

331
00:19:18.407 --> 00:19:19.658
Thanks.

332
00:19:19.741 --> 00:19:21.285
If only it were that easy.

333
00:19:22.870 --> 00:19:27.249
Well… do you have any plans.
Thursday. 4:00 p.m.?

334
00:19:27.332 --> 00:19:29.459
- Q. stop.
- It's not a date.

335
00:19:29.543 --> 00:19:34.715
It's an interview with Marius's dad
for an internship next semester.

336
00:19:34.798 --> 00:19:37.467
His company has a branch in Seoul.

337
00:19:37.551 --> 00:19:39.803
- I don't want to owe Marius anything.
- You won't.

338
00:19:40.304 --> 00:19:42.973
Look. Marius really wants
to make things right with you.

339
00:19:44.057 --> 00:19:45.142
And…

340
00:19:45.642 --> 00:19:46.894
So do I.

341
00:19:47.394 --> 00:19:51.190
I've actually been reaching out to a few
companies owned by former KISS alums.

342
00:19:51.273 --> 00:19:53.692
so while I appreciate the help…

343
00:19:54.526 --> 00:19:55.861
I want to do this on my own.

344
00:19:55.944 --> 00:19:57.237
Of course.

345
00:19:58.071 --> 00:19:59.907
Jin. I only did this because…

346
00:20:01.491 --> 00:20:02.492
I love you.

347
00:20:03.869 --> 00:20:06.788
And I know
there's nothing I can say to prove it.

348
00:20:08.165 --> 00:20:09.833
But maybe I can show you.

349
00:20:10.918 --> 00:20:15.088
And I'll keep showing you. however long
it takes for you to believe me.

350
00:20:16.798 --> 00:20:19.009
Part of me wants to make you grovel.

351
00:20:19.760 --> 00:20:22.054
Like. forever.

352
00:20:22.930 --> 00:20:23.847
But…

353
00:20:24.973 --> 00:20:26.266
I love you too.

354
00:20:27.559 --> 00:20:29.144
I want to trust you again.

355
00:20:29.853 --> 00:20:32.773
Especially since we only have
one semester left together.

356
00:20:35.609 --> 00:20:36.818
"Together?"

357
00:20:39.905 --> 00:20:44.159
<i>Still wondering how we got here</i>

358
00:20:45.160 --> 00:20:49.248
<i>With every mess we made</i>

359
00:20:49.998 --> 00:20:53.669
<i>But all of it still means nothing…</i>

360
00:20:53.752 --> 00:20:56.922
<i>If I can't take your breath away </i>

361
00:20:57.005 --> 00:20:58.590
What are you doing up here?

362
00:20:59.675 --> 00:21:02.010
Just thinking about
how crazy this year's been.

363
00:21:03.136 --> 00:21:04.805
All the changes. and…

364
00:21:06.807 --> 00:21:09.017
It's been quite the journey.

365
00:21:10.227 --> 00:21:12.646
Well. I'm really impressed
with how far you've come.

366
00:21:13.689 --> 00:21:14.690
And…

367
00:21:17.025 --> 00:21:19.361
I'm glad you're getting a second chance.

368
00:21:22.906 --> 00:21:25.617
I also really love this song.

369
00:21:29.079 --> 00:21:31.373
But I think it would be better
if you danced with me.

370
00:21:34.334 --> 00:21:35.752
I would love to.

371
00:21:38.755 --> 00:21:41.675
<i>Your eyes are like weapons</i>

372
00:21:41.758 --> 00:21:44.428
<i>Your lips could teach lessons</i>

373
00:21:44.511 --> 00:21:47.222
<i>Don't use them so reckless</i>

374
00:21:47.306 --> 00:21:49.891
<i>'Cause for you. I'm helpless</i>

375
00:21:49.975 --> 00:21:52.853
<i>You gotta take caution</i>

376
00:21:52.936 --> 00:21:55.605
<i>You know that I'm all in</i>

377
00:21:55.689 --> 00:21:58.608
<i>The chance of me falling</i>

378
00:21:58.692 --> 00:22:01.695
<i>You know that it's often</i>

379
00:22:02.195 --> 00:22:05.407
<i>But if you don't wanna stay…</i>

380
00:22:05.490 --> 00:22:06.575
So…

381
00:22:07.326 --> 00:22:09.119
How does it feel to be 18?

382
00:22:10.037 --> 00:22:11.663
I feel very wise.

383
00:22:13.623 --> 00:22:16.293
Well. would wise old Covey

384
00:22:17.085 --> 00:22:18.462
like to dance?

385
00:22:24.259 --> 00:22:28.305
<i>You're starting up a wildfire</i>
<i>In my head</i>

386
00:22:28.972 --> 00:22:30.891
<i>Hope it's what you meant…</i>

387
00:22:30.974 --> 00:22:32.893
So let me get this straight.

388
00:22:33.560 --> 00:22:37.272
The themed gifts were your idea.

389
00:22:38.065 --> 00:22:40.400
And the camellias.

390
00:22:40.484 --> 00:22:44.363
And here. I totally bought your lie
about going to LA for winter break.

391
00:22:45.072 --> 00:22:46.823
Kitty. I wasn't lying.

392
00:22:47.699 --> 00:22:50.077
I did have a ticket booked to LA.

393
00:22:50.744 --> 00:22:51.953
But I decided

394
00:22:53.288 --> 00:22:54.748
I'd rather be here.

395
00:22:57.834 --> 00:22:59.252
Can I ask you something?

396
00:23:00.587 --> 00:23:01.588
Yeah.

397
00:23:03.298 --> 00:23:06.718
When you applied early decision to NYU.

398
00:23:08.095 --> 00:23:10.889
how did you know
it was the right call for you?

399
00:23:12.015 --> 00:23:13.683
Oh. um…

400
00:23:14.184 --> 00:23:17.062
Well. I kind of fell in love with it
this summer.

401
00:23:17.145 --> 00:23:20.649
And I really love my life in Seoul.

402
00:23:21.441 --> 00:23:25.195
but when we weren't together.

403
00:23:25.946 --> 00:23:28.740
it gave me a chance
to really think about what I want.

404
00:23:28.824 --> 00:23:30.409
- Mm.
- For myself.

405
00:23:31.576 --> 00:23:34.496
And I realized it was NYU.

406
00:23:35.455 --> 00:23:37.874
So I decided to just go for it.

407
00:23:40.043 --> 00:23:41.044
Why?

408
00:23:42.921 --> 00:23:45.132
SOS911 is firing my dad.

409
00:23:46.216 --> 00:23:48.135
They want me to be their manager.

410
00:23:48.218 --> 00:23:50.220
Min Ho. that's huge!

411
00:23:51.012 --> 00:23:55.934
Yes. but I'd have to miss
quite a bit of school next term.

412
00:23:58.562 --> 00:24:00.522
Well. are you gonna take the job?

413
00:24:01.022 --> 00:24:03.150
Honestly. I'm not sure.

414
00:24:07.404 --> 00:24:09.239
What do you think I should do?

415
00:24:14.453 --> 00:24:16.496
Happy birthday. Covey.

416
00:24:20.250 --> 00:24:22.961
<i>I'm not a person</i>
<i>that lets go of control easily.</i>

417
00:24:23.044 --> 00:24:26.089
<i>I like taking the wheel.</i>
<i>and I like knowing where I'm going.</i>

418
00:24:26.173 --> 00:24:28.717
<i>But I learned something</i>
<i>on my 18th birthday.</i>

419
00:24:28.800 --> 00:24:30.886
<i>If you're surrounded by</i>
<i>the people you love.</i>

420
00:24:30.969 --> 00:24:34.264
<i>you can always trust them</i>
<i>to get you exactly where you need to go.</i>

421
00:24:37.726 --> 00:24:39.019
Thank you!

422
00:24:43.899 --> 00:24:48.945
<i>All the city's sleeping</i>

423
00:24:50.155 --> 00:24:52.824
<i>Every street light's calling out…</i>

424
00:24:52.908 --> 00:24:56.036
<i>As quickly as it came.</i>
<i>the semester's over.</i>

425
00:24:56.119 --> 00:24:59.664
<i>I'm halfway to graduation.</i>
<i>halfway to goodbye.</i>

426
00:24:59.748 --> 00:25:02.792
<i>I had so many expectations</i>
<i>coming into my senior year.</i>

427
00:25:02.876 --> 00:25:04.961
<i>I even wrote them all down in a list.</i>

428
00:25:05.045 --> 00:25:07.756
<i>I wanted it to be perfect.</i>

429
00:25:08.298 --> 00:25:09.758
<i>It wasn't.</i>

430
00:25:09.841 --> 00:25:11.676
<i>It was… messy.</i>

431
00:25:11.760 --> 00:25:13.678
<i>Sometimes it hurt.</i>

432
00:25:14.638 --> 00:25:19.017
<i>But it was beautiful.</i>
<i>and I wouldn't change a thing.</i>

433
00:25:19.518 --> 00:25:21.144
<i>Even the surprises.</i>

434
00:25:21.895 --> 00:25:25.315
<i>There may even be more to come.</i>
<i>and I'm okay with that.</i>

435
00:25:26.816 --> 00:25:30.153
<i>Oh. when the lighthouse fires</i>

436
00:25:30.237 --> 00:25:32.739
<i>Feel a world away</i>

437
00:25:33.532 --> 00:25:36.409
<i>Then you just have to remember</i>

438
00:25:36.493 --> 00:25:39.579
<i>That the dark won't last forever</i>

439
00:25:39.663 --> 00:25:41.748
<i>I'm always yours</i>

440
00:25:50.465 --> 00:25:51.800
It's good!

441
00:25:53.635 --> 00:25:55.053
It turned out really well.

442
00:25:55.136 --> 00:25:56.555
Thanks for helping me.

443
00:25:58.557 --> 00:26:01.560
I told my dad I'm pursuing music.

444
00:26:01.643 --> 00:26:02.686
Really?

445
00:26:02.769 --> 00:26:04.104
What'd he say?

446
00:26:04.688 --> 00:26:09.025
He said he spent his whole life
working at a job he hated

447
00:26:09.526 --> 00:26:11.695
and doesn't want that for me.

448
00:26:12.320 --> 00:26:15.865
He would be proud of me
if I spent my life doing what I love.

449
00:26:16.908 --> 00:26:19.035
That's all I ever wanted
to hear from my dad.

450
00:26:22.414 --> 00:26:24.082
He'll come around.

451
00:26:25.166 --> 00:26:27.419
Maybe he will. maybe he won't.

452
00:26:32.299 --> 00:26:35.093
I keep thinking about
what Kitty said to me…

453
00:26:35.176 --> 00:26:37.804
About what I really want for myself.

454
00:26:39.556 --> 00:26:43.393
I've been too focused on
what others expect of me.

455
00:26:44.644 --> 00:26:47.022
Maybe I want to pursue something I love.

456
00:26:53.987 --> 00:26:55.113
Gotta go.

457
00:26:59.576 --> 00:27:00.535
Good luck!

458
00:27:04.122 --> 00:27:05.665
Hey. is Kitty here?

459
00:27:05.749 --> 00:27:07.876
She already left for break.
You just missed her.

460
00:27:07.959 --> 00:27:10.712
But she's taking the subway
to the airport. so you can catch her.

461
00:27:10.795 --> 00:27:12.631
- Right. subway.
- Yeah.

462
00:27:12.714 --> 00:27:14.049
Which subway?

463
00:27:14.841 --> 00:27:15.925
Oh God.

464
00:27:16.009 --> 00:27:18.553
- What? I've never taken one before.
- Never?

465
00:27:18.637 --> 00:27:19.804
Here. take my T-card.

466
00:27:19.888 --> 00:27:21.973
It's the airport line
out of Seoul Station.

467
00:27:22.932 --> 00:27:24.601
Welcome to how the other half lives.

468
00:27:26.019 --> 00:27:28.229
- Great. thank you. Thank you!
- Go. go. go! Bye!

469
00:27:28.313 --> 00:27:29.564
See you next semester!

470
00:27:29.648 --> 00:27:30.857
Good luck!

471
00:28:19.239 --> 00:28:22.867
<i>We've been running circles</i>
<i>Round and doing figure eights</i>

472
00:28:22.951 --> 00:28:26.746
<i>Worried. I was stressing about you</i>
<i>You've been on my brain</i>

473
00:28:26.830 --> 00:28:28.707
<i>I need you to let me know</i>

474
00:28:28.790 --> 00:28:32.210
<i>If you feel the same 'cause I</i>

475
00:28:33.002 --> 00:28:34.337
<i>I</i>

476
00:28:34.421 --> 00:28:37.674
<i>Recognize that we might be</i>
<i>Running out of time</i>

477
00:28:37.757 --> 00:28:42.220
<i>But in your eyes. I've always known</i>
<i>When something isn't right…</i>

478
00:28:43.638 --> 00:28:44.639
Kitty!

479
00:28:48.893 --> 00:28:53.565
{\an8}<i>So before we say XO. goodbye</i>

480
00:28:53.648 --> 00:28:56.693
<i>Let me tell you why</i>

481
00:28:57.277 --> 00:29:00.697
<i>The sun doesn't rise without you</i>

482
00:29:00.780 --> 00:29:04.576
<i>The more I hold the night</i>

483
00:29:05.076 --> 00:29:08.705
<i>The rain wouldn't stop</i>
<i>Pouring down. no</i>

484
00:29:08.788 --> 00:29:11.583
<i>The clouds. they will always cry</i>

485
00:29:11.666 --> 00:29:16.504
<i>Can't take it anymore</i>
<i>Living in this space between</i>

486
00:29:16.588 --> 00:29:20.091
<i>Time will never make it right</i>

487
00:29:20.175 --> 00:29:23.261
<i>'Cause the sun doesn't rise</i>
<i>Without you</i>

488
00:29:23.344 --> 00:29:25.346
<i>By my side</i>

489
00:29:26.681 --> 00:29:29.100
<i>By my side</i>

490
00:29:31.770 --> 00:29:35.356
<i>By my side. without you</i>

491
00:29:36.024 --> 00:29:37.817
<i>What can I do?</i>

492
00:29:37.901 --> 00:29:39.360
<i>You've chosen your place</i>

493
00:29:39.444 --> 00:29:43.072
<i>If this is what you want</i>
<i>Then I will give you your space</i>

494
00:29:43.156 --> 00:29:46.659
<i>But my future feels so dark</i>

495
00:29:46.743 --> 00:29:50.538
<i>Without the one I can't replace</i>

496
00:29:50.622 --> 00:29:55.001
<i>So before you say XO. goodbye</i>

497
00:29:55.084 --> 00:29:58.713
<i>Let me tell you why</i>

498
00:29:58.797 --> 00:30:02.091
<i>The sun doesn't rise without you</i>

499
00:30:02.175 --> 00:30:05.970
<i>The more I hold the night</i>

500
00:30:06.471 --> 00:30:09.933
<i>The rain wouldn't stop</i>
<i>Pouring down. no</i>

501
00:30:10.016 --> 00:30:13.019
<i>The clouds. they will always cry</i>

502
00:30:13.102 --> 00:30:17.982
<i>Can't take it anymore</i>
<i>Living in this space between</i>

503
00:30:18.066 --> 00:30:21.236
<i>- Time will never make it right</i>
- Kitty!

504
00:30:21.319 --> 00:30:26.533
<i>'Cause the sun doesn't rise</i>
<i>Without you by my side</i>

505
00:30:29.369 --> 00:30:30.787
I heard your song.

506
00:30:34.165 --> 00:30:35.458
It's incredible.

507
00:30:35.542 --> 00:30:37.460
I'm so sorry

508
00:30:37.544 --> 00:30:39.921
that it took me so long
to sort myself out.

509
00:30:40.964 --> 00:30:43.883
Covey. I don't want
to stand in the way of your future.

510
00:30:44.843 --> 00:30:47.220
And I don't know
what my future holds. but…

511
00:30:48.680 --> 00:30:50.306
I want it to be with you.

512
00:30:51.307 --> 00:30:54.269
And I couldn't let you go
without telling you that.

513
00:30:55.562 --> 00:30:57.230
Or without saying…

514
00:30:58.815 --> 00:31:00.024
I love you.

515
00:31:02.485 --> 00:31:03.862
You what?

516
00:31:04.821 --> 00:31:06.030
I love you.

517
00:31:09.033 --> 00:31:10.493
I love you too.

518
00:31:10.577 --> 00:31:13.329
<i>Started in the strangest way</i>

519
00:31:13.413 --> 00:31:15.039
<i>Didn't see it coming</i>

520
00:31:15.123 --> 00:31:18.001
<i>Swept up in your hurricane</i>

521
00:31:18.084 --> 00:31:20.503
<i>Wouldn't give it up for nothing</i>

522
00:31:20.587 --> 00:31:23.006
<i>Now I'm all caught up</i>
<i>In the highs and the lows</i>

523
00:31:23.089 --> 00:31:25.758
<i>It's a shock to my system</i>

524
00:31:25.842 --> 00:31:29.387
<i>I don't wanna run away. so I stayed</i>

525
00:31:29.470 --> 00:31:33.141
<i>My head gets messy when I try to hide…</i>

526
00:31:33.224 --> 00:31:35.560
<i>I don't know what this means</i>
<i>for Min Ho and me.</i>

527
00:31:35.643 --> 00:31:37.604
<i>I don't know what our future holds.</i>

528
00:31:37.687 --> 00:31:39.772
<i>I don't have a plan this time.</i>

529
00:31:39.856 --> 00:31:41.649
<i>But if I've learned anything this year.</i>

530
00:31:41.733 --> 00:31:46.362
<i>it's that sometimes. it's just better</i>
<i>to let go and see what happens.</i>

531
00:31:55.330 --> 00:31:56.998
I like first class.

532
00:31:57.749 --> 00:32:00.168
Mm. Technically. this is business class.

533
00:32:01.210 --> 00:32:03.004
Don't get posh on me. Covey.

534
00:32:07.216 --> 00:32:09.969
It's going to be freezing in Portland.
isn't it?

535
00:32:10.053 --> 00:32:11.387
We'll get you some warm clothes.

536
00:32:11.471 --> 00:32:14.432
I think you would look
really cute in a flannel.

537
00:32:15.224 --> 00:32:18.227
I can't wait to see the city
that made Kitty Song Covey.

538
00:32:19.228 --> 00:32:20.313
Yeah?

539
00:32:20.396 --> 00:32:24.400
Well. if you thought LJ was something.
just wait till you meet my dad.

540
